Magic Rumble - A strategic building and unit management game

version 0.1:
- Initial game implementation with Love2D engine
- Main menu with Play Game and Quit buttons
- Strategic gameplay where players place buildings and units fight autonomously
- Map generation with organic, randomly-shaped rooms connected by hallways
- Grid-based building placement system allowing multiple buildings per room
- Five building types: Barracks, Archery Range, Mage Tower, Shop, Inn
- Three unit types with different combat styles: Warriors (melee), Archers (ranged), Mages (spell)
- Room capture mechanics with progress bars and strategic implications
- King units that must be protected, with movement controls
- Hearts system - lose hearts when enemies touch your king
- Gold economy with income from controlled rooms
- AI opponent that builds strategically and competes for territory
- Camera controls: WASD/arrow keys for movement, right-click drag
- Zoom controls: Q/E keys and mouse wheel (0.25x to 2x zoom range)
- Building preview system with red/green placement validation
- Unit pathfinding and exploration AI to seek out enemies
- Collision detection to prevent units walking through each other
- Turn-based income every 10 seconds
- Building mana system that resets when rooms are captured
- Map connectivity guarantee - all rooms are reachable
- Randomized maps using OS time seed for unique layouts each game
- Keyboard shortcuts: 1-5 keys for quick building selection
- Visual grid system for precise building placement

